name: v0.23.3
body:
Bug fixes:
- Fix a regression that caused xenorchestra_cloud_config resource to fail on newer versions of Xen orchestra (#206)

name: v0.23.2
body:
Bug fixes:
- Fix a regression that caused `xenorchestra_vm` resource deletion to fail on newer versions of Xen orchestra (#198)
- Fix misspelling in the documentation (#192)

name: v0.23.1
body:
Enhancements:
- Improved the `xenorchestra_vm` resource documentation to reflect how
  to template cloud-init config (#181)
- Added test sweepers for all remaining resources (#187). This improves
  the test suite quality by cleaning up dangling resources on failures.

Bug fixes:
- Fixed a bug that prevented non admin users from managing VMs within a
  resource set (self-service VMs) - #171
- Improved various documentation mistakes (#183, #186)

name: v0.23.0
body:
Enhancements:
- Non admin users are able to use the `xenorchestra_user` data source to
  retrieve details about their own user accounts.

Bug Fixes:
- Updated the `xenorchestra_vm` documentation to highlight that the resource supports custom create
  timeouts

name: v0.22.0
body:
Improvements:

Added more arguments to the xenorchestra_vm resource:
- blocked_operations
- exp_nested_hvm
- videoram
- hvm_boot_firmware
- vga
- start_delay

See vm resource documentation for more details.

name: v0.21.0
body:
Improvements:
- Extend host data source arguments (#160)
- Add `xenorchestra_vm` data source (#165)

Bug fixes:
- Fix flaky test
- Use StringInSlice function defined in the terraform sdk

name: v0.20.1
body: - Add more attributes to the xenorchestra_sr data sourc

name: v0.20.0
body:
Features:
  - Added PXE boot support to the xenorchestra_vm resource

Breaking Changes:
  - Upgraded terraform-provider-sdk to v2. This removes support for
      terraform 0.11 and earlier

name: v0.19.1
body:
Bug Fixes:
- Prevent ordering of tags from causing erroneous terraform diffs (#147)

name: v0.19.0
body:
Features:
- Allow vm resource to update cpu and memory for a VM. With the ability to do it without stopping the VM when possible (#144). See the vm resource documentation for more details
- Add `hosts` data source (#142)
Bug fixes:
- Update all data sources to return an error if the infrastructure is not found (#141)

name: v0.18.0
body:
Features:
- Add support for terraformer (#96)

name: v0.17.1-rc2
body:
Changes:
- The release binaries are now built through Github actions

name: v0.17.0
body:
Changes:
- Build the provider's release binaries with Github actions

name: v0.16.1
body:
Bug fix:
- Ensure create, update and delete resource timeouts work for the vm resource (#135)

name: v0.16.0
body:
Features:
- Add VDI data source (#127)
- Add support for creating VMs with diskless templates with an ISO
  (#128)

Breaking changes:
- 386 and ARM6 binaries are no longer created as part of the release
  process (#130)

name: v0.15.0
body:
Features:
- Added `ipv4_addresses` and `ipv6_addresses` attributes to the vm resource (more details on the documentation on registry.terraform.io) - Addresses #49 and #112  
- Added `host` data source #120

name: v0.14.0
body: - Added cloud config data source (#113)

name: v0.13.1
body:
Bug fixes:
- Fixed an issue where a properly formatted mac address would cause vm creation or VIF updates to fail (#114)

name: v0.13.0
body:
- Added support for tags on the vm resource (#107)
- Added support for host_affinity attribute on vm resource (#110)

name: v0.12.0
body:
Improvements:
- Allow the provider to disable SSL verification (for users that have XO installed with self signed certs) - #106

name: v0.11.2
body:
Bug fixes:
- Fixed an issue where `memory_max` was not stored in the state of the `xenorchestra_vm` resource

name: v0.11.1
body: - Update `xenorchestra_vm` resource docs to include the `name_description` attribute in the `disk` object.

name: v0.11.0
body: - Added support for updating `name_description` and `name_label` attributes on `xenorchestra_vm`'s disks

name: v0.10.0
body:
- Added `xenorchestra_acl` resource for managing ACLs
- Added `xenorchestra_user` data source

name: v0.9.1
body: - Added additional (cloud-init) network config in the xenorchestra_vm resource (fixes #34)

name: v0.9.0
body:
- Fix issue where VMs could only be created with a single disk (#33)
- Implement additional and removal of disks in `xenorchestra_vm` resource
- Implement attaching and disconnecting disks in `xenorchestra_vm` resource

name: v0.8.0
body:
- Fix bug where the network configuration of the VM resource is not ordered in the way it’s defined (Issue #76)
- Fix bug in terraform provider that prevents the a detached VIF from showing a diff (Issue #56)

name: v0.7.3
body: - Fixes an issue where a connection error to the XO api causes a panic (#81)

name: v0.7.2
body: - Fixes an issue where deleting a resource that terraform managed would not handle recreating the resource (#79)

name: v0.7.1
body: - Fixed a bug that would cause inconsistent terraform plans in certain situations (#77)

name: v0.7.0
body: - Updated the `cloud_config` attribute on the vm resource to be optional (#13)

name: v0.6.1
body: - Fixed a bug that would cause inconsistent terraform plans in certain situations (#77)

name: v0.6.0
body:
- Pif, Template and storage repository data source panics when there are multiple matches (#66)
- Unify the pattern of retrieving XoObjects from the XO api (#52)
- Resolve PV driver issues with the terraform acceptance test VM template (#57)
- Test suite improvements to make it easy to run the tests against any XO deployment
Update syntax errors in the documentation.

name: v0.5.0
body:
- Add resource set data source
- Add resource set resource
- Add support for resource sets in the vm resource

v0.4.0
